The search for "flakehub input url format flake.nix" returned the following summary:
The standard URL format for FlakeHub inputs in a `flake.nix` file is:

```nix
https://flakehub.com/f/:org/:project/:version-requirement.tar.gz
```

### Breakdown of the URL Format
*   **`:org`**: The name of the organization (e.g., `NixOS`).
*   **`:project`**: The name of the flake repository (e.g., `nixpkgs`).
*   **`:version-requirement`**: A SemVer version constraint or wildcard (e.g., `0.1.2`, `0.1.*`, or `*`).

### Examples
*   **Specific Version:** `https://flakehub.com/f/NixOS/nixpkgs/0.2405.0.tar.gz`
*   **Wildcard (Latest Minor):** `https://flakehub.com/f/NixOS/nixpkgs/0.2405.*.tar.gz`
*   **Latest Overall:** `https://flakehub.com/f/NixOS/nixpkgs/*.tar.gz`

### Usage in `flake.nix`
You use these URLs in the `inputs` attribute set of your `flake.nix` just like any other input:

```nix
{
  inputs = {
    nixpkgs.url = "https://flakehub.com/f/NixOS/nixpkgs/0.2405.*.tar.gz";
    fh.url = "https://flakehub.com/f/DeterminateSystems/fh/*.tar.gz";
  };

  outputs = { self, nixpkgs, fh }: {
    # Your flake outputs...
  };
}
```

### Tips for FlakeHub Inputs
*   **Automatic Conversion:** You can use the FlakeHub CLI (`fh`) to manage these inputs for you. Running `fh convert` in your project directory will automatically attempt to convert your existing GitHub-based inputs into FlakeHub URLs.
*   **Predictable Upgrades:** Because FlakeHub supports SemVer, using version ranges (like `0.1.*`) allows you to receive bug fixes and updates automatically when you run `nix flake update`, without needing to track specific Git revisions manually.
*   **FlakeHub CLI:** You can install the CLI tool itself using a FlakeHub URL:
    `nix shell "https://flakehub.com/f/DeterminateSystems/fh/*.tar.gz"`
